brace
=====

Compatibility
-------------
- Fedora 29 (preferred)
- Arch Linux
- EL 7/8
- openSUSE (very basic support)

Contents
--------
Installed
	00-brace*				= GNOME/Cinnamon/MATE: change default settings
	21-disable-connectivity-check.conf	= NetworkManager: disable connectivity checking
	30-mac-randomization.conf		= NetworkManager: enable MAC address randomization
	60-restrict.conf			= kernel: restrict dmesg and ptrace
	blacklist-dma.conf			= kernel: blacklist modules that provide direct memory access externally
	blacklist-usbnet.conf			= kernel: blacklist modules that allow for USB networking
	brace-arch-installer.sh			= Arch: package installer
	brace-fedora-enable-auto-updates.sh	= Fedora: enables DNF automatic updates
	brace-fedora-installer.sh		= Fedora: package installer
	brace-fedora-installer-base.sh		= Fedora: simplified package installer
	brace-fedora-remover.sh			= Fedora: package remover
	brace-fedora-update-system.sh		= Fedora: update system using dnf-plugin-system-upgrade
	brace-supplemental-changes.sh		= GNOME: change extra default settings
	dnu.service				= kernel: systemd target to toggle linux-hardened's deny_new_usb sysctl
	helpers.sh				= profile: adds helper aliases
	iwlwifi.sh				= kernel: iwlwifi: enables link aggregation for increased performance
	userjs-*.js				= Firefox: change default settings
Package Creation
	brace.install				= pacman helper script
	brace.spec				= RPM specfile
	PKGBUILD				= pacman PKGBUILD
Repository Necessaries
	LICENSE
	README

